{"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140":{"concepts":["AgentMemory hooks (SessionStart, UserPromptSubmit, PreToolUse) trigger context injection","Dual compression paths: synthetic (zero-LLM, always available) vs LLM-powered (AUTO_COMPRESS optional)","Memory hierarchy: raw observations ŌåÆ synthetic compression/indexing ŌåÆ LLM consolidation ŌåÆ durable lessons/memories","Context injection multi-stage filtering: project-scoped priority, importance thresholds, token budgeting","Consolidation pipeline: requires 3+ observations sharing concept, groups by concept, caps LLM calls at 10/run","Memory tab displays consolidated memories from crystallize/consolidate/reflect; timeline/sessions/activity tabs show raw observations","Lesson sources: manual (user-created), crystal (crystallize function), consolidation (consolidate function)","Embedding model: local Xenova/transformers (all-MiniLM or equivalent) for zero-API dependency vector search","BM25 and vector search are pure statisticalŌĆöno model inference or API calls during retrieval","Observation persistence: state_store.db filesystem storage + REST API access independent of LLM provider"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T20:36:27.306Z","filesModified":["~/.agentmemory/.env","~/.zshrc","~/.zshrc.bak-20260627-125006","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/config.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/triggers/api.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/consolidate.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/context.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/enrich.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/compress-synthetic.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/crystallize.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/lessons.ts","/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/mcp/tools-registry.ts","/Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm/data/state_store.db/"],"keyDecisions":["Migrated ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from ~/.zshrc shell config to ~/.agentmemory/.env for centralized secrets management and environment isolation","Confirmed retrieval/injection paths are independent of LLM providerŌĆöBM25 and local embeddings enable memory recall without external API calls","Validated that observations persist in state_store.db regardless of AUTO_COMPRESS or LLM availability; compression pipeline is optional enhancement","Identified lesson/memory creation requires explicit API calls (POST /agentmemory/lessons, /memories, /consolidate) or manual crystallize/reflect functionsŌĆöno automatic creation on hook triggers"],"narrative":"The session focused on configuring an Anthropic API key for the AgentMemory system and investigating why the dashboard Memories tab appeared empty despite storing 750+ observations. Key findings: observations are stored in a state database and indexed locally (no LLM required), but consolidation into durable memories requires an LLM provider for the summarize function. The user configured their API key from console.anthropic.com into ~/.agentmemory/.env, enabling the LLM-backed consolidation pipeline. Investigation revealed the memory system uses dual paths: synthetic compression (zero-LLM, always available) for indexing and search, and optional LLM compression (AUTO_COMPRESS) for richer summaries. The Memories tab displays consolidated memories created via the consolidate/crystallize/reflect pipelines, distinct from raw observations stored in the state database.","observationCount":123,"project":"agentmemory","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","title":"AgentMemory API Configuration and Memory Consolidation Debugging"},"92617014-5d50-4f04-ba98-da6ee9fa198d":{"concepts":["HTTP 429 rate limiting","Email verification code resend","HttpErrorResponse status code handling","i18n translation management","Angular error handling in async operations"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T19:35:21.477Z","filesModified":["frontend/src/app/features/auth/login-email-code/login-email-code.component.ts","frontend/public/i18n/public/en.json","frontend/public/i18n/public/zh.json"],"keyDecisions":["Detect HTTP 429 status code in frontend resendCode() method to distinguish rate-limit errors from other failures, providing specific user feedback about the 60-second cooldown requirement","Add dedicated translation keys for both generic resend errors and cooldown-specific errors to support proper i18n across language variants","Implement error handling in component using HttpErrorResponse to access status codes from failed HTTP requests"],"narrative":"Fixed email verification code resend functionality to properly handle rate-limiting. When users attempt to resend a verification code within 60 seconds, the backend returns HTTP 429, which the frontend now detects and displays a user-friendly cooldown message instead of a generic error. Added error handling in the login-email-code component's resendCode() method, implemented HTTP 429 status detection with HttpErrorResponse, and added localized error messages in both English and Chinese translation files.","observationCount":71,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"92617014-5d50-4f04-ba98-da6ee9fa198d","title":"Email Verification Code Resend Rate-Limit Handling"},"bc74e163-6da3-4a1d-89a8-740a6cb0c102":{"concepts":["activeEngagementStatus: Client's current workflow state derived from latest non-COMPLETED engagement, with fallback to COMPLETED or null","Spring Data JPA derived query methods for engagement state lookup with status filtering and tax year ordering","OpenSpec superpowers-driven schema: requirements ŌåÆ proposal ŌåÆ specs ŌåÆ design ŌåÆ tasks with contract-based evaluation gates","Test-driven development workflow: RED (failing tests) ŌåÆ GREEN (implementation) ŌåÆ EVAL (external evaluator scoring)","UI consolidation: removing separate nav items in favor of contextual action buttons within feature-specific lists","Server-side activeEngagementStatus computation to ensure consistency and avoid client-side staleness","Navigation pattern migration: navbar dropdown link to per-row action button in table for improved discoverability","External evaluator subagent for contract validation and scoring across Specification, Runtime, and Code dimensions","E2E test coverage for new UI features validating workflow feature accessibility and component state transitions","Type alignment between backend and frontend: EngagementStatus enum in both layers for strong typing of workflow state"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T22:13:01.004Z","filesModified":["backend/src/main/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/dto/ClientDto.java","backend/src/main/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/service/ClientService.java","backend/src/main/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/domain/ClientEngagementRepository.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/service/ClientServiceTest.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/controller/ClientControllerTest.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/messaging/controller/AdminMessageControllerTest.java","backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/client/controller/DocumentControllerTest.java","frontend/src/app/core/models/client.model.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/clients/admin-clients.component.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/clients/admin-clients.component.html","frontend/src/app/features/admin/clients/admin-clients.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/shared/navbar/navbar.component.html","frontend/src/app/shared/navbar/navbar.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/client-messages/admin-client-thread-view.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/client-messages/admin-client-threads.component.spec.ts","frontend/src/app/features/admin/client-documents/admin-client-documents.component.spec.ts","e2e/workflow-to-client-mgmt.spec.ts","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/requirements.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/proposal.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/specs/admin-workflow-ui/spec.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/specs/client-management/spec.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/design.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/tasks.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/contracts/group-1.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/contracts/group-2.md","openspec/changes/workflow-to-client-mgmt/eval-log.md","docs/log/2026-06-27.md"],"keyDecisions":["activeEngagementStatus defined as the status of the most recent non-COMPLETED engagement by tax year; if all are COMPLETED, return COMPLETED; if no engagements exist, return null. Implemented via Spring Data JPA derived query methods on ClientEngagementRepository.","Use Spring Data derived query `findFirstByClientIdAndStatusNotOrderByTaxYearDesc` with fallback pattern to compute activeEngagementStatus server-side for performance and consistency rather than client-side filtering.","Move workflow functionality from navbar dropdown link to per-client action button in client list table, reducing navbar clutter and improving discoverability while consolidating related features.","Add \"Workflow State\" column to admin client list table with status badge rendering to provide at-a-glance visibility of engagement status and enable batch operations without context-switching.","Organize change as three groups with external evaluation gates: Group 1 (backend activeEngagementStatus logic), Group 2 (frontend UI + navbar), Group 3 (E2E tests)ŌĆöensures quality and contract compliance.","Add EngagementStatus enum type alias to frontend ClientDto model to match backend enum and enable strong typing of activeEngagementStatus field and workflow state filtering.","Used OpenSpec superpowers-driven schema for systematic requirements capture, proposal, specs, design, and task breakdown with contract-based evaluation and external evaluator scoring."],"narrative":"Completed a comprehensive three-group OpenSpec change that consolidated workflow management from a standalone navbar item into the client management interface. Group 1 implemented backend support by adding an `activeEngagementStatus` field to ClientDto using Spring Data JPA derived queries to fetch each client's most recent non-COMPLETED engagement. Group 2 enhanced the frontend admin client list with a new \"Workflow State\" column displaying engagement status, removed the standalone \"Workflow\" navbar link, and added a per-client workflow action button. Group 3 added E2E Playwright tests validating the new UI behavior. All 308 backend unit tests, ~156 frontend unit tests, and 5 E2E tests pass; external evaluators scored both Groups 1 and 2 as PASS (99/100 and 98.4/100).","observationCount":1532,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"bc74e163-6da3-4a1d-89a8-740a6cb0c102","title":"Workflow-to-Client-Mgmt: Consolidate workflow into client management UI"},"cbb9884f-4076-4830-8f5d-1ed5a8e58546":{"concepts":["Memory persistence and lesson creation","Confidence scoring in memory systems","Memory decay and reinforcement tracking","User identity management","MCP agent memory tools"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T20:31:19.671Z","filesModified":[],"keyDecisions":["Used memory_lesson_save tool instead of direct memory_save for explicit lesson creation, allowing for structured persistence with confidence scoring and decay tracking","Tagged the memory entry with \"user-name\" and \"gary\" for improved searchability and contextual retrieval"],"narrative":"The session focused on testing and configuring the AI agent's memory system. A lesson was created to remember the user's name \"Gary\" with high confidence (1.0) and tagged with relevant metadata. The agent successfully used the memory_lesson_save tool to persist this information, demonstrating proper integration with the memory persistence layer. The lesson was assigned a decay rate of 0.05 and source type of \"manual\" for tracking purposes.","observationCount":7,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"cbb9884f-4076-4830-8f5d-1ed5a8e58546","title":"Memory System Setup - User Identity Lesson Created"},"ef220526-7344-435e-b72c-ee4732ba534d":{"concepts":["Claude plugin management system","superpowers plugin","plugin version tracking","Claude configuration directory","project-specific plugin installation"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T20:46:39.399Z","filesModified":["/Users/gwang/.claude/plugins/installed_plugins.json"],"keyDecisions":["Used Python JSON parsing to extract specific plugin version information from installed_plugins.json, filtering for plugins associated with the accounting-firm project path","Navigated Claude's plugin configuration at ~/.claude/plugins/ rather than the initial assumption of ~/.claude/plugins directory structure"],"narrative":"The user queried the version of the superpowers plugin installed in their Claude environment. The session involved navigating the Claude configuration directory structure to locate plugin metadata, specifically examining the installed_plugins.json file. Through a series of filesystem explorations and JSON parsing, the agent identified that the superpowers plugin (superpowers@claude-plugins-official) was installed and extracted its version information for an accounting-firm project located at /Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm.","observationCount":7,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"ef220526-7344-435e-b72c-ee4732ba534d","title":"Investigate Superpowers Plugin Version in Claude Environment"},"10e14017-2f3e-4428-9177-17ccd5eb1fb1":{"concepts":["OpenSpec workflow with strict phase boundaries (exploreŌåÆreviewŌåÆproposeŌåÆapply)","Multiple engagements per client per tax year with unique (client_id, tax_year, name) constraint","Engagement entity with mandatory name field and mutable note field","Route parameter migration from {taxYear} to {id} for engagement identification","Admin UI \"New Engagement\" dialog and \"Change Status\" note editing capability"],"createdAt":"2026-06-27T23:29:24.395Z","filesModified":["openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/requirements.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/proposal.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/design.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/tasks.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/specs/client-engagement-workflow/spec.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/specs/admin-workflow-ui/spec.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/specs/client-portal-ui/spec.md","openspec/changes/engagement-name-note/eval-log.md"],"keyDecisions":["Enforce unique constraint on (client_id, tax_year, name) instead of (client_id, tax_year) to allow multiple engagements per client per year while preventing duplicate names within the same year","Switch engagement routes from path parameter `{taxYear}` to `{id}` to uniquely identify engagements when multiple exist per tax year","Make engagement name mandatory at creation time (taxpayer name for PERSONAL, business name for CORPORATE/SELF_EMPLOYED) and make note field mutable via Change Status dialog","Follow strict OpenSpec workflow phases: requirements must be REVIEWED before proceeding to proposal/specs/design/tasks artifacts"],"narrative":"The session explored the accounting-firm codebase to understand the current engagement and workflow data model, then created a comprehensive OpenSpec change proposal for allowing multiple engagements per client per tax year. The requirements document was reviewed and moved into the OpenSpec change directory. Following the strict OpenSpec workflow, all five artifacts (requirements, proposal, specs, design, and tasks) were generated with detailed specifications for database schema changes, API modifications, and UI updates across both admin and client portals. The completed change artifacts were committed to git.","observationCount":116,"project":"accounting-firm","sessionId":"10e14017-2f3e-4428-9177-17ccd5eb1fb1","title":"engagement-name-note OpenSpec proposal completion"}}┤°␀␀╠┴  